Christophe Raffalli wrote:
> 
> I was writing emacs lisp last week and thought that it would be nicer to be
> able to write it in OCaml.
> 
> I know efun, but will it be hard to interface Emacs/XEamcs and OCaml ? The
> problem is how to treat Lisp variables, callbacks in both directions
> and interaction between the two GCs. It seems hard, but may be there is a
> simple solution that I do not see ...

It may be possible, but I believe it is hard. There was a project to
link Perl into Emacs (http://john-edwin-tobey.org/perlmacs/) but it it
has switched to a pipe interface, which may be an easier option if
someone wanted to do the same thing with OCaml.

